<p><b>Peter (Harmer) Lovesey</b> (born 1936), also known by his pen name <b>Peter Lear</b>, is a <a href="/wiki/British_people" title="British people">British</a> writer of <a href="/wiki/Historical_mystery" title="Historical mystery">historical</a> and <a href="/wiki/Detective_fiction" title="Detective fiction">contemporary detective</a> novels and short stories. His best-known series characters are Sergeant Cribb, a <a href="/wiki/Victorian_era" title="Victorian era">Victorian</a>-era police detective based in London, and Peter Diamond, a modern-day police detective in <a href="/wiki/Bath,_Somerset" title="Bath, Somerset">Bath</a>.</p>
<p></p>
