<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Biography">Biography</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Peter_Lovesey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Biography">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Peter Lovesey lives near <a href="/wiki/Chichester" title="Chichester">Chichester</a>. His son Phil Lovesey also writes crime novels. His son was born in 1963 and worked as an English teacher at <a href="/wiki/Wolverhampton_Grammar_School" title="Wolverhampton Grammar School">Wolverhampton Grammar School</a> until the end of the autumn 2012.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Bibliography">Bibliography</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Peter_Lovesey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Bibliography">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>Lovesey's novels and stories mainly fall into the category of entertaining puzzlers in the "<a href="/wiki/Golden_Age_of_Detective_Fiction" title="Golden Age of Detective Fiction">Golden Age</a>" tradition of mystery writing.</p>
<p>Most of Peter Lovesey's writing has been done under his own name. However, he did write three novels under the pen name Peter Lear.</p>
<p>Lovesey's novels and short stories have won him a number of awards, including both the <a href="/wiki/Gold_Dagger" title="Gold Dagger">Gold and Silver Daggers</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Crime_Writers%27_Association" title="Crime Writers' Association">Crime Writers' Association</a>, of which he was chairman in 1991/92.<a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.thecwa.co.uk/daggers/gold.html">[2]</a> In 2000, he received the <a href="/wiki/Cartier_Diamond_Dagger" title="Cartier Diamond Dagger">Cartier Diamond Dagger</a> Award for lifetime achievement in crime writing.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
